spanGrp.span: there was a mister who crashed against a horse;
jeska estee pekaga dul ñerö mãĩ wö kenã' kó estee (hm) kabayö mẽ
he ran and went into a tiger’s cage
je tunã' jẽk pakkachá-wã estee jie pakkachá-wã mãĩ nãmã tsõ ska
and there the door closed and he could not get out.
ñerö jeska jũkö kötenã'-wã ka í desãũ
He was there and saw a tiger sleeping.
Ñerö (_) este í dul-te mãĩ nãmã (_) nãmã je (m) sũã'-wã ñerö jeska nãmã (_) (_) kablali köpö
It did not see him, but then it woke up;
Je ka wã í sunẽ ñerö je shkinã'-ka
he saw him wake up and put his head into a hole;
jie të sũã'-ra shkinã'-ka ñerö jie (_) wö pakká-wã estee kal jenẽi nã
he did not see the tiger,
Jeska ka jie-wa (_) nãmã (_) nãmã kablali (_) e-gla sũã'
but when he saw him, he started to run away and the tiger roared on his face.
ñerö je ka/ jie (m) (_) í sũã'-ra jie jie tunã' ñerö mãĩ estee nãmã anã' í wö nã
Then there came a woman, a lady,
ñerö mãĩ í alaglöwa datu estee mãĩ pemina dajũ
and he told her to open the door for him;
të ĩã í shá-ite estee „¡ba wã jũkö yöjãwã s-ĩã“
but she fainted and fell down.
Suddenly a dog came by that barked a lot at them;
Ñerö estee jekẽinska (_) chichi dajũ je ar koü í (_) wö nã
the man took his foot out of the hole and the dog bit him in the foot;
ñerö estee mãĩ í klö pakká-wã je kal wöjenẽi nã Ñerö estee chichi të í kwá í klöga
it thus pulled him so, so he scolded the dog and the dog left.
Ñerö je sigá ñerö jie të chichi juñã' ñerö (m) chichi mẽnẽũ-mĩ
At that point the girl woke up again and ran away;
Jekẽ'inska ja/ estee pe (r) pebusi je shkinã'-ka-nẽ etabaglö je mẽnẽũ tunã'-te
she opened the door for him,
but now he would not go;
instead, he came toward the tiger;
Ñerö je (_) beteũ-te beteũ-te-nẽ estee mãĩ nãmã kablali ska
the tiger roared on his face.
Ñero nãmã anã' í wö nã
So, he climbed up on a light pole
ñerö jie mẽnẽũ tunã' je mẽnẽũwãũ estee lus poste mẽ
and he said uh… that he was like a monkey and that he wanted to fly like a bird.
Ñerö jeska estee (m) she-ite jie rö estee jie rö (_) estee jie rö mono bi jamẽ jie rö estee jie (_) jũr estee dö bi
there was a woman there who he spoke to.
ñerö jeska estee alaglöwa dul jeska je ra í ktö'-gẽ
ñerö jeska estee jeska jie-wa mẽnẽũ-lo-mĩ
